  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Tortuous-- torturous road back to Carpathia-- now, we are-- we are in-- in-- Rosh Hashanah in the city of Horodenka.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were at the place of Berl Gefner.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Horodenka, the city, had already, at that time, a Judenrat and a-- a very, very large Jewish community that was supporting the Hungarian refugees.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One day after Rosh Hashanah, my brother Tsvi and I went over to the-- to the-- Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we told them that we have a letter from my Ukrainian priest to-- to help us out in our-- in our journey-- return back to the Carpathia.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if it is possible, they could give us some paper to-- also that we should have some kind of paper to cover that we were returning to Carpathia.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for our greatest surprise, the-- the office of the Judenrat in Horodenka told us that we should come back tomorrow, and they will have a permission paper issued by the German command.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Up to this day-- the next day-- we-- my brother Tsvi and I-- we always were the ones that-- my brother Moshe was with the children.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he had stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were the ones that were going out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Up to this day, I am-- I am wondering if we came to the Judenrat, and here they gave us a document that had the stamp with the swastika on it, signed by a German Oberleutant, and our names, and it says that we are permitted to proceed to the Carpathian border-- to the Carpathian to-- to Hungarian border.",
      "word_count": 59
    }
  ],
